                            <comment id="14270512" author="arafalov" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2015 03:51:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, the README.txt has the reversed version of the usage:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;java -jar -Dc=&amp;lt;collection_name&amp;gt; post.jar *.xml&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;b&gt;java -?&lt;/b&gt;, the &lt;b&gt;-D&lt;/b&gt; params need to come before &lt;b&gt;-jar&lt;/b&gt;. Strangely, the example actually works as given on Java 8/Mac. But I think it should still be consistent with other locations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
